  "body": "*This is an implementation/Usage question.\r\n\r\nI'd like to use the native [Element.scrollIntoView API](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element/scrollIntoView) in my React app to scroll to components from code.\r\nTo use that, I need reference to the HTML Element I want to scroll into.\r\n\r\nUsing React's [ref prop](https://reactjs.org/docs/refs-and-the-dom.html#adding-a-ref-to-a-dom-element) returns reference of React component, and not the HTMLElement DOM instance, so I can't use the desired API with it.\r\n\r\nIs there a way to get access to the HTML DOM element in order to use the native scrollIntoView API? \r\n\r\nVersions in use:\r\nReact 16\r\nChrome browser (latest)",
